1
00:03:44,357 --> 00:03:47,485
We were working with local
military anti-drug forces...

2
00:03:47,560 --> 00:03:51,428
a search and destroy
mission on cocaine labs.

3
00:03:51,497 --> 00:03:54,364
Lt. Dobbs and I had trained
local pilots in Cobras...

4
00:03:54,434 --> 00:03:56,265
for their own
strike forces.

5
00:03:56,336 --> 00:03:58,361
This is Snake Two...

6
00:03:58,471 --> 00:04:00,371
entering sector 407 9.

7
00:04:00,440 --> 00:04:02,465
Advise operations
of our position.

8
00:04:02,575 --> 00:04:06,636
Wilco, Dobbs.
How's the view up front?

9
00:04:06,713 --> 00:04:11,047
I'll be glad
when we get out of this canyon.

10
00:04:11,284 --> 00:04:13,616
I was flying wing
with Captain Tejada.

11
00:04:13,686 --> 00:04:15,950
Lt. Dobbs,
the other American...

12
00:04:16,022 --> 00:04:18,388
was with
Captain Mendez.

13
00:04:18,458 --> 00:04:22,360
Between the 2 Cobras was
a Black Hawk helicopter...

14
00:04:22,428 --> 00:04:24,794
with a support team
of American...

15
00:04:24,831 --> 00:04:27,299
and South American
D.E.A. agents.

16
00:04:27,367 --> 00:04:29,767
It was our
<i>4</i>th mission as a team.

17
00:04:29,836 --> 00:04:32,430
We were entering
a new sector.

18
00:04:32,505 --> 00:04:34,735
It was rumored
among the locals...

19
00:04:34,807 --> 00:04:37,799
that this was an area
of offensive cartel activity...

20
00:04:37,910 --> 00:04:40,310
but we were
used to such rumors.

21
00:04:40,380 --> 00:04:42,746
We were 5 miles
from the objective...

22
00:04:42,815 --> 00:04:45,648
when we saw the Scorpion
attack helicopter.

23
00:04:46,853 --> 00:04:50,448
Dobbs, bogey at your 1 2..00.!

24
00:04:51,491 --> 00:04:53,356
Dobbs.!

25
00:04:54,861 --> 00:04:58,422
Black Hawk,
get the hell out of there.

26
00:04:58,498 --> 00:05:01,763
The Black Hawk
began evasive action...

27
00:05:01,834 --> 00:05:04,530
but the Scorpion
was too fast...

28
00:05:04,637 --> 00:05:07,572
heavily armed,
and hard to find.

29
00:05:07,640 --> 00:05:10,541
The pilot was
the best I'd ever seen.

30
00:05:11,844 --> 00:05:14,904
I tried to pull the Scorpion
away from the Black Hawk...

31
00:05:14,981 --> 00:05:16,778
but to no use.

32
00:05:16,849 --> 00:05:19,409
He was a cold killer.

33
00:05:24,824 --> 00:05:26,758
Tejada!

34
00:05:27,760 --> 00:05:29,660
Wake up,
goddamn it!

35
00:05:29,729 --> 00:05:31,663
I took the controls...

36
00:05:31,731 --> 00:05:35,030
and crossed over the top of the
Scorpion before he could fire.

37
00:05:35,101 --> 00:05:38,002
I made it
out of the area.

38
00:05:42,575 --> 00:05:45,544
 We said the cartel
was up to something.

39
00:05:45,578 --> 00:05:49,036
I'm not blaming anybody.
We're on the same side.

40
00:05:49,115 --> 00:05:51,640
We have some
decisions to make.

41
00:05:51,718 --> 00:05:54,710
Thank you, Mr. Preston.
That will be all.

42
00:05:57,724 --> 00:06:00,124
May I say
something?

43
00:06:04,697 --> 00:06:07,393
Go ahead.

44
00:06:07,433 --> 00:06:10,061
I volunteered to fly
with the anti-drug forces.

45
00:06:10,136 --> 00:06:12,661
I watched the men
in those choppers...

46
00:06:12,739 --> 00:06:16,436
risk their lives for their
families and their country.

47
00:06:16,542 --> 00:06:20,410
The cartel has them outpaid,
outmanned, and outgunned.

48
00:06:20,446 --> 00:06:23,415
Knowing that,
they still went out.

49
00:06:23,449 --> 00:06:26,475
They didn't
stand a chance.

50
00:06:26,552 --> 00:06:29,885
They're heroes,
and they should be avenged.

51
00:06:29,956 --> 00:06:32,117
It's more
complicated than that.

52
00:06:32,191 --> 00:06:34,716
I think it's
very simple.

53
00:06:34,794 --> 00:06:37,729
They killed our people
and they killed our friends.

54
00:06:37,797 --> 00:06:40,732
Their drugs kill
Americans every day.

55
00:06:40,800 --> 00:06:43,598
It's a war, and it's
our duty to fight.

56
00:06:43,669 --> 00:06:46,001
Thank you.
You are excused.

57
00:06:54,814 --> 00:06:58,113
 Does anyone else
feel as frustrated as I do?

58
00:06:58,151 --> 00:07:01,985

Yes, but it's a complex problem.

59
00:07:02,054 --> 00:07:05,990
 We have an executive mandate
to stop the drug cartel.

60
00:07:06,025 --> 00:07:09,552
That pilot out there has
the clearest take on this mess.

61
00:07:09,629 --> 00:07:12,792
We are at war, and we deal
with the problem as such.

62
00:07:12,832 --> 00:07:15,824
Should we go back to the
same sort of operation?

63
00:07:15,902 --> 00:07:19,030
The D.E.A. is fighting
a war with its hands tied...

64
00:07:19,138 --> 00:07:21,470
and we're losing.

65
00:07:21,541 --> 00:07:22,940
Not anymore.

66
00:07:23,009 --> 00:07:25,443
General Olcott,
I want a task force.

67
00:07:25,511 --> 00:07:28,537
- I want that operation taken out.
- Yes, sir.

68
00:07:30,683 --> 00:07:33,015
My Apache crews are
trained for ground support...

69
00:07:33,085 --> 00:07:35,178
not for
air-to-air combat.

70
00:07:35,254 --> 00:07:38,189
If this enemy helicopter
is as good as we hear...

71
00:07:38,257 --> 00:07:40,782
I need help
to bring him down.

72
00:07:40,860 --> 00:07:43,192
Anything
you want.

73
00:07:43,262 --> 00:07:46,754
Who is this enemy pilot,
and what's his support like?

74
00:07:46,833 --> 00:07:49,768
I've got to have
Brad Little and his team.

75
00:07:49,836 --> 00:07:52,202
I want them
at Fort Mitchell.

76
00:07:52,271 --> 00:07:55,206
This is a
need-to-know operation.

77
00:07:55,274 --> 00:07:58,243
All reports
eyes-only to me.

78
00:07:58,478 --> 00:08:00,173
And that Preston...

79
00:08:00,213 --> 00:08:03,580
see if you can
keep him in the mix.

80
00:08:03,649 --> 00:08:05,207
Will do.

81
00:08:05,952 --> 00:08:07,476
Preston?

82
00:08:07,553 --> 00:08:09,487
Yes, sir.

83
00:08:10,590 --> 00:08:12,956
You've seen
this bogey work.

84
00:08:13,025 --> 00:08:15,550
Can the Apache
stand up to it?

85
00:08:15,595 --> 00:08:18,120
It is the only
aircraft that will.

86
00:08:18,197 --> 00:08:21,496
How soon can you
fly the bird?

87
00:08:21,567 --> 00:08:24,502
I'm scheduled to start hands-on
at Fort Mitchell.

88
00:08:24,570 --> 00:08:27,198
Olcott wants you
in this mission.

89
00:08:27,273 --> 00:08:29,264
I believe in you.

90
00:08:29,542 --> 00:08:32,778
- Can you handle it?
- You can count on me.

91
00:08:57,737 --> 00:09:00,069
At ease.
Take a seat.

92
00:09:05,177 --> 00:09:08,203
We've got a lot to do,
so I'll make this brief.

93
00:09:08,281 --> 00:09:11,250
This is our new
combat instructor pilot...

94
00:09:11,284 --> 00:09:13,752
Chief Warrant Officer
Brad Little.

95
00:09:13,819 --> 00:09:17,084
He'll bring us up to speed
on air combat maneuvers.

96
00:09:19,325 --> 00:09:21,293
You men know
all about...

97
00:09:21,327 --> 00:09:23,625
air-to-ground
technique.

98
00:09:23,696 --> 00:09:27,257
Now you have a new
objective in your lives...

99
00:09:27,300 --> 00:09:30,929
and that is to become masters
of air-to-air combat tactics.

100
00:09:31,003 --> 00:09:34,166
When we have
mastered these tactics...

101
00:09:34,240 --> 00:09:36,765
we will use them
to seek out...

102
00:09:36,809 --> 00:09:40,108
the forces of evil,
and kill them deader than hell.

103
00:09:42,315 --> 00:09:44,112
We're lucky men.

104
00:09:44,183 --> 00:09:46,708
We face the opportunity
of a lifetime.

105
00:09:46,786 --> 00:09:49,721
I do not expect you to
throw away this opportunity.

106
00:09:49,789 --> 00:09:52,724
I expect you to improve
every minute of my time...

107
00:09:52,792 --> 00:09:55,852
by becoming the best
air-to-air pilots in the world.

108
00:09:55,928 --> 00:09:59,125
You will fight as teams
of Gunners and pilots...

109
00:09:59,198 --> 00:10:02,964
each more dependent on the other
than to their own mama.

110
00:10:06,739 --> 00:10:10,004
Our mission has
the highest national priority.

111
00:10:10,076 --> 00:10:12,237
I can't stress
that enough.

112
00:10:12,311 --> 00:10:14,836
We're going against
an enemy...

113
00:10:14,914 --> 00:10:16,973
who's defending
his own territory.

114
00:10:17,083 --> 00:10:19,142
The clock
is running, folks...

115
00:10:19,251 --> 00:10:21,719
and it's
running fast.

116
00:10:21,787 --> 00:10:24,255
Group!
Attention!

117
00:10:24,323 --> 00:10:26,416
Carry on.

118
00:10:29,662 --> 00:10:31,687
Looks like a fine
group of aviators.

119
00:10:31,764 --> 00:10:34,096
They are that,
Brad.

120
00:10:34,166 --> 00:10:37,067
Preston showed extraordinary
courage in South America.

121
00:10:37,136 --> 00:10:40,071

Pay special attention to him.

122
00:10:40,139 --> 00:10:43,074
Somebody called it
a flying race car with guns...

123
00:10:43,142 --> 00:10:45,201
but that's
bullshit.

124
00:10:45,277 --> 00:10:47,677
It's not
that simple.

125
00:10:47,780 --> 00:10:49,714
Put your hands
here and there...

126
00:10:49,782 --> 00:10:51,750
put your feet
here and here.

127
00:10:51,851 --> 00:10:55,150
Do not step
here or there.

128
00:11:01,894 --> 00:11:04,988
That's it.
Crawl right in there.

129
00:11:06,132 --> 00:11:09,067
Riding at 1 50 knots
through the treetops...

130
00:11:09,135 --> 00:11:13,128
is like having your ass strapped
to the nose of a bullet.

131
00:11:13,205 --> 00:11:15,901
You will be flying
like a bat out of hell...

132
00:11:15,975 --> 00:11:17,875
shooting at the enemy...

133
00:11:17,910 --> 00:11:20,310
dodging bullets,
missiles, rocks...

134
00:11:20,379 --> 00:11:22,347
spears, ducks,
and geese.

135
00:11:22,415 --> 00:11:24,940
Sounds like
a full-time job.

136
00:11:25,017 --> 00:11:27,884
You're gonna be as busy
as a 3-peckered goat.

137
00:11:28,421 --> 00:11:30,355
Let's get to it.

138
00:11:30,423 --> 00:11:32,391
[ Preston ]
You really get into this, don't you?

139
00:11:32,425 --> 00:11:35,986
- I love it to death.
- I can tell.

140
00:11:36,062 --> 00:11:38,030
Heaven,
here we come.

141
00:11:38,097 --> 00:11:41,066
- What do we do first?
- Is this a quiz?

142
00:11:41,100 --> 00:11:43,398
You whole
life's a quiz.

143
00:11:43,436 --> 00:11:45,836
Tell me the first
order of business.

144
00:11:45,905 --> 00:11:49,136
Program the nav systems,
enter the laser codes...

145
00:11:49,208 --> 00:11:51,870
punch in target
and Doppler coordinates...

146
00:11:51,944 --> 00:11:55,311
initialize weapon systems,
and optimize F.L.I.R. sensors.

147
00:11:55,381 --> 00:11:59,078
Good. Let's see if the
damn thing will start.

148
00:12:08,527 --> 00:12:11,394
[ Little ] It has a roll rate
of 1 50 degrees per second...

149
00:12:11,464 --> 00:12:14,831
so if you need to duck,
dive, or disappear...

150
00:12:14,900 --> 00:12:17,892
this buggy will do it before
your brain can think it up.

151
00:12:20,973 --> 00:12:24,340
We could crash this aircraft
at 20 G's and survive...

152
00:12:24,410 --> 00:12:26,810
but I am not
gonna prove it to you.

153
00:12:28,981 --> 00:12:30,175
Darn.

154
00:12:30,282 --> 00:12:34,013
[ Little ] The missiles
can take out a door at 5 miles.

155
00:12:34,086 --> 00:12:37,180
In air-to-air combat,
your best weapon is agility...

156
00:12:37,256 --> 00:12:40,919
and this gunship is agile,
mobile, and hostile.

157
00:12:42,495 --> 00:12:43,962
Great.

158
00:12:48,234 --> 00:12:50,759
[ Little ]
How's the ride?

159
00:12:50,836 --> 00:12:52,770
[ Preston ]
Unreal!

160
00:13:06,852 --> 00:13:08,046
God.

161
00:13:08,120 --> 00:13:11,556
You usually hide in a hole
and cause things to blow up...

162
00:13:11,791 --> 00:13:14,157
but now you'll
move like a thief...

163
00:13:14,193 --> 00:13:16,559
keep your nose down...

164
00:13:16,796 --> 00:13:20,232
then come out of nowhere
and blow your enemy to pieces.

165
00:13:24,236 --> 00:13:27,069
- Sound like fun?
- Yeah.

166
00:13:55,534 --> 00:13:57,468
- Sir?
- Yeah?

167
00:13:57,536 --> 00:13:59,527
That was
totally cool.

168
00:13:59,605 --> 00:14:01,573
I'd marry
that thing.

169
00:14:01,607 --> 00:14:04,974
I'll give away
the bride. Buzzard!

170
00:14:05,044 --> 00:14:08,411
MeetJake Preston,
part of the Apache force.

171
00:14:08,514 --> 00:14:11,176
This is Scott Buzz,
my chief scout I.P....

172
00:14:11,250 --> 00:14:13,514
and Billie Guthrie,
his copilot.

173
00:14:15,454 --> 00:14:17,422
Billie Lee Guthrie.

174
00:14:17,456 --> 00:14:19,424
I think I've
heard of you.

175
00:14:19,491 --> 00:14:21,288
How you doin'?

176
00:14:22,428 --> 00:14:24,623
I do fine.

177
00:14:24,864 --> 00:14:27,264
How about a drink
this evening?

178
00:14:27,299 --> 00:14:29,529
Jake,
not a chance.

179
00:14:31,570 --> 00:14:33,504
''Not a chance.''

180
00:14:33,572 --> 00:14:36,439
- How much flight time did you log?
- 2.3.

181
00:14:36,508 --> 00:14:39,238
- What?
- 2.3, sir.

182
00:14:40,646 --> 00:14:42,307
2.3.

183
00:14:42,414 --> 00:14:47,078
- You have a problem with women in the army?
- Not with all of them.

184
00:14:47,152 --> 00:14:49,120
Just that one.

185
00:14:50,556 --> 00:14:53,491
I'll see you
at 07 00.

186
00:14:55,594 --> 00:14:58,529
[ Daniels ] The cartel has made
the decision to go...

187
00:14:58,597 --> 00:15:02,363
on the offensive and expand
into neighboring countries.

188
00:15:02,434 --> 00:15:05,164
They've brought in Cuban
arms and an advisory team.

189
00:15:05,237 --> 00:15:08,934
They've hired Eric Stoller,
a crack pilot and mercenary...

190
00:15:09,008 --> 00:15:11,602
to ride shotgun
on their missions.

191
00:15:11,677 --> 00:15:15,943
His terrorist training
was in Europe and North Korea.

192
00:15:16,048 --> 00:15:18,573
Now he sells his expertise
to the highest bidder.

193
00:15:18,651 --> 00:15:22,018
In this tape, our D.E.A. team
thought they had him cornered...

194
00:15:22,087 --> 00:15:24,021
but it was a setup.

195
00:15:24,089 --> 00:15:27,217
Stoller acted as a decoy
and drew them in.

196
00:15:28,527 --> 00:15:32,190
There's a booby-trapped bomb
waiting for those men.

197
00:15:32,264 --> 00:15:35,961
[ Daniels ] Watch for the box
at the bottom of the screen.

198
00:15:38,570 --> 00:15:41,698
Everyone in Washington
knows what we're up against.

199
00:15:41,941 --> 00:15:43,932
This guy's
a killer.

200
00:15:44,009 --> 00:15:46,637
We need to support
the D.E.A....

201
00:15:46,745 --> 00:15:49,976
and that means dealing
with Stoller air-to-air.

202
00:15:50,015 --> 00:15:52,609
I'd like to be considered
for the Apache task force.

203
00:15:52,685 --> 00:15:54,619
I need you here.

204
00:15:54,687 --> 00:15:56,655
Nobody better
than I am.

205
00:15:56,689 --> 00:15:59,351
It's your job to convey
that knowledge and experience...

206
00:15:59,458 --> 00:16:02,621
to these young pilots.

207
00:16:02,695 --> 00:16:04,526
When the time comes to use the experience,
I want to fly this mission.

208
00:16:04,596 --> 00:16:07,531
- Is Janet joining you?
- This afternoon.

209
00:16:07,599 --> 00:16:10,727
- You want to fly and get shot at?
- Affirmative.

210
00:16:10,970 --> 00:16:13,734
We can't afford
to lose you.

211
00:16:19,078 --> 00:16:21,171
-Just one drink.
- No.

212
00:16:21,213 --> 00:16:23,738
It's your birthday.
Let's have fun.

213
00:16:23,983 --> 00:16:26,508
I'm 40 years old,
and I want to go home.

214
00:16:26,552 --> 00:16:29,646
At ease, Little.

215
00:16:29,722 --> 00:16:34,091
Everybody does what they
want on their birthday.

216
00:16:34,159 --> 00:16:36,491
Surprise!

217
00:16:36,562 --> 00:16:39,224
Oh, no!
No!

218
00:16:46,505 --> 00:16:49,133
[ Humming ''Hail to the Chief' ]

219
00:16:50,376 --> 00:16:53,038
There you go.

220
00:16:53,112 --> 00:16:55,239
Go for it.

221
00:16:55,314 --> 00:16:57,805
This is
really stupid.

222
00:17:01,320 --> 00:17:04,050
- Yeah!
- All right!

223
00:17:17,669 --> 00:17:20,297
How about
that drink now?

224
00:17:20,372 --> 00:17:21,669
Interested?

225
00:17:23,409 --> 00:17:26,572
Uh, no, thanks.

226
00:17:31,283 --> 00:17:34,150
'For he's a jolly
good fellow '

227
00:17:34,219 --> 00:17:36,619
No, Billie.

228
00:17:36,655 --> 00:17:40,751
'For he's a jolly
good fellow '

229
00:17:40,826 --> 00:17:44,353
' Which nobody
can deny ''

230
00:17:47,566 --> 00:17:50,228
[ Little ]
Welcome to the future.

231
00:17:50,302 --> 00:17:52,736
Descend the stairway
and turn right.

232
00:17:52,805 --> 00:17:55,797
At the first platform,
enter the big black box.

233
00:17:55,874 --> 00:17:58,172
Make ready
for war.

234
00:18:03,849 --> 00:18:06,750
[ Preston ]
Want some gum, Breaker?

235
00:18:06,819 --> 00:18:09,754
No, thanks.

236
00:18:09,822 --> 00:18:12,450
Little, how about you?
Strawberry gum?

237
00:18:12,558 --> 00:18:14,253
No.

238
00:18:14,326 --> 00:18:16,191
It's delicious.

239
00:18:16,261 --> 00:18:17,558
Come on,Jake.

240
00:18:17,629 --> 00:18:21,224
This simulator will do
anything the Apache will do.

241
00:18:21,300 --> 00:18:24,292
It will also do anything
your enemy will do.

242
00:18:24,369 --> 00:18:28,601
Good, because I have
a pocket full of quarters.

243
00:18:28,674 --> 00:18:30,403
Let's go play.

244
00:18:30,476 --> 00:18:32,774
- Set up X-ray.
- Yes, sir.

245
00:18:32,845 --> 00:18:35,643
[ Little ]
This program is called ''X-ray. ''

246
00:18:35,681 --> 00:18:38,650
All babies need to crawl
before they walk.

247
00:18:38,684 --> 00:18:41,653
All systems are up.
The pilot has the controls.

248
00:18:41,687 --> 00:18:44,747
The name of the
