- Yeah.

752
00:50:02,099 --> 00:50:04,624
Some things should
never change.

753
00:50:04,701 --> 00:50:07,192
I put your suitcase
in the trunk.

754
00:50:07,270 --> 00:50:09,636
- What are you doing?
- Driving.

755
00:50:09,706 --> 00:50:12,004
You knew that,
didn't you?

756
00:50:13,477 --> 00:50:15,707
Okay, hot-rod.

757
00:50:15,779 --> 00:50:19,215
Put the pedal to the metal
and let's see what you got.

758
00:50:22,652 --> 00:50:24,643
[ Tires Screech ]

759
00:50:24,721 --> 00:50:27,087
Whoa,
good night!

760
00:50:27,157 --> 00:50:29,455
[Jake ]
Wouldn't it be terrific...

761
00:50:29,526 --> 00:50:32,461
if we could get a house
here and live together?

762
00:50:32,529 --> 00:50:35,293
[ Billie ]
There's nothing out here.

763
00:50:35,365 --> 00:50:38,596
- Then I'd have you all to myself.
- Oh,Jake.

764
00:50:50,447 --> 00:50:52,745
- [Jake ] Why'd you change?
- [ Billie ] Less to take off.

765
00:50:52,816 --> 00:50:56,217
[Jake ]
Let's skip dinner.

766
00:50:58,555 --> 00:51:01,490
God, it is
beautiful.

767
00:51:03,827 --> 00:51:06,694
You're beautiful.

768
00:51:08,665 --> 00:51:10,656
Ha, ha.

769
00:51:10,700 --> 00:51:13,533
Patience.
Anticipation.

770
00:51:13,603 --> 00:51:15,798
Food.

771
00:51:18,508 --> 00:51:20,840
I learned
something today.

772
00:51:21,078 --> 00:51:23,103
- In the bag?
- Yeah.

773
00:51:23,180 --> 00:51:25,205
About dominance.

774
00:51:25,282 --> 00:51:27,807
Put your right hand
out to the side.

775
00:51:27,884 --> 00:51:29,749
Close your
left eye.

776
00:51:29,820 --> 00:51:33,881
Put your left hand
out to that side...

777
00:51:34,157 --> 00:51:36,318
and close
your right eye.

778
00:51:41,765 --> 00:51:43,596
Jake.

779
00:51:43,667 --> 00:51:48,104
[''Do You Remember?'']
' We never talked about it '

780
00:51:48,171 --> 00:51:53,199
'But I hear
the blame is mine '

781
00:51:53,276 --> 00:51:58,407
'And I'd call you up
to say I'm sorry '

782
00:51:58,482 --> 00:52:02,782
'But I wouldn't want
to waste your time '

783
00:52:02,853 --> 00:52:05,378
' 'Cause I love you '

784
00:52:05,489 --> 00:52:08,287
'But I can't
take anymore '

785
00:52:08,391 --> 00:52:10,882
' There's a look
I can't describe '

786
00:52:11,161 --> 00:52:14,562
'In your eyes '

787
00:52:14,664 --> 00:52:19,658
'If we could try
like we tried before '

788
00:52:19,736 --> 00:52:22,933
' Would you keep on
tellin'me those lies '

789
00:52:23,173 --> 00:52:28,133
' Tellin'me lies '

790
00:52:29,746 --> 00:52:33,739
'Do you remember '

791
00:52:33,817 --> 00:52:37,344
'Do you remember '

792
00:52:40,290 --> 00:52:44,226
'Do you remember '

793
00:52:45,962 --> 00:52:49,454
' Through all
of my life '

794
00:52:50,767 --> 00:52:54,328
'In spite of
all the pain '

795
00:52:55,839 --> 00:53:00,367
' You know how people
are funny sometimes '

796
00:53:00,443 --> 00:53:04,539
' Theyjust can't wait
to get hurt again '

797
00:53:04,614 --> 00:53:07,742
' Tell me,
do you remember ''

798
00:53:15,559 --> 00:53:17,925
I hear there's
a great place...

799
00:53:17,961 --> 00:53:20,486
a couple miles
up a dirt road...

800
00:53:20,564 --> 00:53:24,261
- where we can swim sans clothes.
- I gotta get back.

801
00:53:24,334 --> 00:53:27,235
No. Today is sangria day.

802
00:53:27,304 --> 00:53:29,238
I can't.

803
00:53:29,306 --> 00:53:32,400
I've got a F.L.I.R. flight
with Scott in 2 hours.

804
00:53:32,475 --> 00:53:36,411
Just call the buzz man
and tell him you have plans.

805
00:53:36,479 --> 00:53:38,811
You want to make
the mission, right?

806
00:53:38,882 --> 00:53:42,340
If you had a choice between
a flight with Little...

807
00:53:42,419 --> 00:53:46,947
- or a picnic with me, what would you do?
- Do I have to ask first?

808
00:53:47,224 --> 00:53:50,853
If you ask me first, I'll
go anywhere you tell me.

809
00:53:50,927 --> 00:53:53,225
You go alone.

810
00:53:53,296 --> 00:53:55,230
Good thing
about the army.

811
00:53:55,298 --> 00:53:57,664
I only take orders
from my superiors.

812
00:53:57,734 --> 00:54:00,362
You drive a scout.
I drive the Apache.

813
00:54:00,437 --> 00:54:02,530
Therefore,
I am your superior.

814
00:54:02,606 --> 00:54:04,972
Get in and I'll
drive you home.

815
00:54:07,677 --> 00:54:09,645
Come on,Jake.

816
00:54:09,679 --> 00:54:12,045
I'm driving!

817
00:54:14,985 --> 00:54:16,646
No!

818
00:54:19,022 --> 00:54:20,956
Thank you.

819
00:54:23,860 --> 00:54:27,318
I'm sorry about
the sangria.

820
00:54:32,969 --> 00:54:35,904
Don't you ever
want me to win?

821
00:54:35,972 --> 00:54:37,701
No.

822
00:54:45,882 --> 00:54:48,874

Today you are entering...

823
00:54:48,918 --> 00:54:52,285
the final phase of
aerial combat training.

824
00:54:52,355 --> 00:54:54,915
You will engage
in air-to-air combat...

825
00:54:54,991 --> 00:54:57,585
with your
flight instructors.

826
00:54:57,661 --> 00:55:00,297
Your scores today will be
the determining factor...

827
00:55:00,297 --> 00:55:04,028
for selection to
the Apache task force.

828
00:55:04,100 --> 00:55:06,295
Good luck,
troopers.

829
00:55:07,404 --> 00:55:10,339
Thanks for getting me
through the bag.

830
00:55:10,407 --> 00:55:12,898
It's my job.
You've done very well.

831
00:55:12,976 --> 00:55:14,967
I'm glad
to see it.

832
00:55:15,045 --> 00:55:17,343
Just so you know...

833
00:55:17,414 --> 00:55:20,611
I will be kicking
your ass today.

834
00:55:20,684 --> 00:55:23,084
Good.
All right!

835
00:55:26,389 --> 00:55:29,552
[ Little ] This is Rattler,
ready for a full day.

836
00:55:29,626 --> 00:55:33,062
 Proceed with Stinger
to sector kilo.

837
00:55:33,129 --> 00:55:36,860
This is Stinger.
Roger. Out.

838
00:55:47,610 --> 00:55:50,545
[ Little ] Let's go to our corners
and come out fighting.

839
00:55:50,613 --> 00:55:53,446
[ Breaker]
These guys are serious.

840
00:55:54,551 --> 00:55:57,850
- Breaker, you like history?
- No.

841
00:55:57,921 --> 00:56:00,981
You better start,
because we're about to make it.

842
00:56:01,057 --> 00:56:02,752
Bring 'em on.

843
00:56:15,772 --> 00:56:18,070
[ Little ]
Jump ball, kids.

844
00:56:18,141 --> 00:56:20,769
Let's see who
comes down with it.

845
00:56:20,810 --> 00:56:22,801
[ Breaker ]
Get me in position.

846
00:56:24,781 --> 00:56:28,774
[Jake ] You want position?
You got position.

847
00:56:30,987 --> 00:56:33,114
That kid's good.

848
00:56:35,992 --> 00:56:38,392
I can't lock him.

849
00:56:38,461 --> 00:56:41,862
[ Rice ] He's got position on us.

850
00:56:41,931 --> 00:56:43,831
Not bad for
old-timers.

851
00:56:43,933 --> 00:56:46,458
[ Rice ]
Old-timers, my ass.

852
00:56:52,942 --> 00:56:55,206
Those guys
can fly.

853
00:56:55,445 --> 00:56:57,675
Now, Breaker.

854
00:56:57,714 --> 00:56:59,648
Let's get 'em.

855
00:56:59,682 --> 00:57:01,843
Get me closer,Jake.

856
00:57:02,886 --> 00:57:05,218
- I got lock.
- He's locking on us.

857
00:57:05,455 --> 00:57:07,480
Not for long.

858
00:57:07,524 --> 00:57:09,685
I can't lock him.

859
00:57:09,759 --> 00:57:12,455
[ Little ]
Look alive, Rice.

860
00:57:14,030 --> 00:57:16,521
[ Little ]
Good-bye, try again.

861
00:57:21,137 --> 00:57:23,662
Hang on, rice man.

862
00:57:23,706 --> 00:57:25,833
Let's see if they
can keep up with this.

863
00:57:26,709 --> 00:57:28,506
Where'd
they go?

864
00:57:28,578 --> 00:57:31,547
- Where?
- I don't know.

865
00:57:31,581 --> 00:57:34,015
[Jake ]
Clever, Chief.

866
00:57:36,019 --> 00:57:37,816
Let's do it.

867
00:57:40,857 --> 00:57:43,223
[ Little ]
Get ready, Rice.

868
00:57:43,259 --> 00:57:45,227
We're gonna
park it here.

869
00:57:45,462 --> 00:57:47,657
I've lost him,Jake.

870
00:57:47,730 --> 00:57:49,755
He's vertical,
over the top.

871
00:57:51,201 --> 00:57:54,659
- Let's get 'em.
- He'll pop through that notch.

872
00:57:54,737 --> 00:57:57,069
[Jake ]
He's hiding in a hole.

873
00:57:57,140 --> 00:58:00,007
I'll give him
vertical with a twist.

874
00:58:03,246 --> 00:58:06,113
[Jake ]
Look who we found.

875
00:58:06,182 --> 00:58:07,672
''Hasta la bye-bye.''

876
00:58:07,750 --> 00:58:09,217
Nose down,
Breaker.

877
00:58:09,285 --> 00:58:10,980
- Lock.
- Now!

878
00:58:11,054 --> 00:58:13,284
[ Breaker ]
Missiles's gone.

879
00:58:13,523 --> 00:58:15,684
Shit!

880
00:58:15,758 --> 00:58:18,886
He's toast.
Great flying.

881
00:58:18,962 --> 00:58:22,489
Rattler, they just
notified your next of kin.

882
00:58:22,565 --> 00:58:25,659
I got your next ofkin.

883
00:58:25,768 --> 00:58:27,633
Well done, boys.

884
00:58:27,704 --> 00:58:29,103
Let's get supper.

885
00:58:29,205 --> 00:58:32,606
[ Little ]
Good flying, Preston.

886
00:58:32,642 --> 00:58:36,544
Intelligence reports the cartel
offensive is set to launch.

887
00:58:36,613 --> 00:58:40,105
All the major players are there,
but we don't know for how long.

888
00:58:40,183 --> 00:58:42,913
We can't let them slip
through our fingers.

889
00:58:42,952 --> 00:58:45,921
- How much time do we have?
- We must move immediately.

890
00:58:45,955 --> 00:58:51,086
- We have less than 2 <i>4</i> hours
to eliminate this threat.
- Any word on Stoller?

891
00:58:51,160 --> 00:58:54,596
He's there, making sure
we don't get near them.

892
00:58:57,133 --> 00:58:59,761
Morning, troopers.
Let's do it.

893
00:59:00,770 --> 00:59:03,136
Task force,
attention!

894
00:59:03,172 --> 00:59:06,699
At ease.
Listen up.

895
00:59:06,776 --> 00:59:10,303
In 2 4 hours, you'll be asked
to use what you've learned here.

896
00:59:10,547 --> 00:59:12,879
Our mission is
to fly support...

897
00:59:12,949 --> 00:59:15,645
for a D.E.A. operation
of critical importance..

898
00:59:15,718 --> 00:59:19,347
Operation Fire Bird.
We launch immediately.

899
00:59:19,589 --> 00:59:22,217
We move out
tomorrow morning....

900
00:59:22,292 --> 00:59:26,160
for a staging area
in South America.

901
00:59:26,195 --> 00:59:28,720
Once we're
on the ground...

902
00:59:28,798 --> 00:59:31,961
you'll get your
operations order.

903
00:59:32,068 --> 00:59:34,764
What I can
tell you now...

904
00:59:34,837 --> 00:59:37,829
is that we will
be going air-to-air...

905
00:59:37,874 --> 00:59:42,208
against a Scorpion attack
helicopter and its backup.

906
00:59:42,278 --> 00:59:44,678
There'll be officials
on hand down there...

907
00:59:44,714 --> 00:59:46,682
to arrest
cartel leaders.

908
00:59:46,716 --> 00:59:49,082
Our job is
to make damn sure...

909
00:59:49,152 --> 00:59:51,177
they get
that chance.

910
00:59:51,254 --> 00:59:54,121
That's all.
Let's get hot.

911
00:59:55,191 --> 00:59:58,058
- Congratulations.
- Thank you, Colonel.

912
00:59:58,127 --> 01:00:00,994
- Good luck.
- Right,Jake.

913
01:00:01,030 --> 01:00:04,295
Brad, I've reviewed
the gun-camera tapes...

914
01:00:04,367 --> 01:00:06,733
from your
training flights.

915
01:00:06,836 --> 01:00:10,704
Every man has got his
place of maximum effect.

916
01:00:10,740 --> 01:00:13,300
Brad Little's is
with this task force...

917
01:00:13,376 --> 01:00:16,709
flying the mission.
You're my flight leader.

918
01:00:20,249 --> 01:00:22,308
I knew that.

919
01:00:28,024 --> 01:00:30,618
I want to
talk to you.

920
01:00:30,693 --> 01:00:35,426
- We can talk on the flight down.
- What do you mean?

921
01:00:35,665 --> 01:00:38,327
On the flight
to South America.

922
01:00:38,401 --> 01:00:40,926
How the hell
did that happen?

923
01:00:41,004 --> 01:00:43,097
I asked and
A.K. cleared it.

924
01:00:43,206 --> 01:00:45,674
You're going
into combat?

925
01:00:45,742 --> 01:00:48,074
I don't believe
I'm hearing this.

926
01:00:48,111 --> 01:00:51,012
You think it's fine
for me to be a pilot...

927
01:00:51,080 --> 01:00:53,207
when there's
nothing at stake...

928
01:00:53,249 --> 01:00:55,774
but dangerous missions
are only for men.

929
01:00:55,852 --> 01:00:58,719
Thanks,Jake.
I have my orders.

930
01:00:58,755 --> 01:01:02,782
Why is it so hard
for you to understand...

931
01:01:02,859 --> 01:01:04,918
that I just don't
want you to get hurt?

932
01:01:04,994 --> 01:01:08,725
You, my friend,
have to accept it.

933
01:01:08,798 --> 01:01:10,823
''My friend''?

934
01:03:10,253 --> 01:03:13,313
[ Daniels ] The Bisante cartel
has been amassing heavy arms...

935
01:03:13,389 --> 01:03:16,187
for an attack on
a friendly government.

936
01:03:16,225 --> 01:03:20,093
Every operation
that the D.E.A...

937
01:03:20,196 --> 01:03:23,063
and our South American allies
have mounted has been blown away...

938
01:03:23,132 --> 01:03:25,532
- by Eric Stoller.
- They're airlifting...

939
01:03:25,802 --> 01:03:29,499
some major figures in the
cartel under Stoller's cover.

940
01:03:29,572 --> 01:03:32,905
The local government is tired of
having their army chewed up...

941
01:03:32,975 --> 01:03:34,237
by this guy.

942
01:03:34,310 --> 01:03:36,244
They've asked
for your help.

943
01:03:36,312 --> 01:03:38,246
They're counting
on you.

944
01:03:38,281 --> 01:03:40,442
On your feet.
Get some sleep.

945
01:04:30,900 --> 01:04:33,892
- Sleep well?
- Hell, no.

946
01:04:34,003 --> 01:04:35,937
What do
you think?

947
01:04:36,005 --> 01:04:38,940
It all depends on things
we don't know right now.

948
01:04:39,008 --> 01:04:43,502
You train and you
know you're capable...

949
01:04:43,579 --> 01:04:47,140
but when it comes time,
you wonder what you'll do;

950
01:04:47,216 --> 01:04:49,616
whether you'll take it up
or bring it down...

951
01:04:49,685 --> 01:04:51,949
or whether you'll
ever see an orange again.

952
01:04:52,021 --> 01:04:53,648
Makes for
a long night.

953
01:04:53,890 --> 01:04:56,222
That night's been around
for thousands of years...

954
01:04:56,292 --> 01:04:58,658
full of men waiting
to go into battle.

955
01:04:58,895 --> 01:05:01,659
I think they've all been
talking all night long.

956
01:05:01,931 --> 01:05:04,559
Yeah.

957
01:05:04,634 --> 01:05:08,092
You got chops you
haven't even dreamed of.

958
01:05:08,170 --> 01:05:11,196
Your instincts and
training will take over.

959
01:05:11,274 --> 01:05:14,368
Count on it.
You had a brilliant teacher.

960
01:05:14,443 --> 01:05:17,105
I've been pretty
arrogant with you.

961
01:05:17,179 --> 01:05:19,010
Mm-hmm.

962
01:05:19,048 --> 01:05:21,573
I know I'm great,
but you're the best.

963
01:05:21,651 --> 01:05:25,087
No, you're better.
I can't learn anymore.

964
01:05:25,154 --> 01:05:27,349
Every time we went up
I kept thinking...

965
01:05:27,423 --> 01:05:30,358
''How'd that kid
figure that one out?''

966
01:05:30,426 --> 01:05:32,656
You're a natural.

967
01:05:32,728 --> 01:05:35,424
You've got
a lot of talent.

968
01:05:36,699 --> 01:05:39,725
How about that roll-out
you did during the fly-off?

969
01:05:40,002 --> 01:05:44,234
- Only you could do that.
- I'm not saying I'm not a genius.

970
01:05:44,307 --> 01:05:47,242
I joined the army for
the same reason you did:

971
01:05:47,310 --> 01:05:51,007
to kick ass, like in
the old war movies.

972
01:05:51,080 --> 01:05:54,049
That's what I'm
looking for in you.

973
01:05:54,083 --> 01:05:56,142
An All-American hero...

974
01:05:56,218 --> 01:05:58,379
with his heart and
brain wired together...

975
01:05:58,454 --> 01:06:01,252
cooking full tilt
for freedom and justice.

976
01:06:01,324 --> 01:06:04,259
It's the corniest story
in the whole world.

977
01:06:04,360 --> 01:06:07,329
By God, this could
be a happy day.

978
01:06:11,100 --> 01:06:13,762
[ P.A. System ]
We're under attack.!

979
01:06:14,003 --> 01:06:16,733
Let me repeat,
we are under attack.!

980
01:06:16,973 --> 01:06:19,441
Billie,
Colonel...

981
01:06:19,508 --> 01:06:21,408
incoming
missiles.!

982
01:06:21,477 --> 01:06:23,468
Let's get 'em
in the air!

983
01:06:28,684 --> 01:06:31,084
Get the helicopters
in the air!

984
01:06:47,303 --> 01:06:49,635
Get up,
get up!

985
01:06:49,705 --> 01:06:52,401
[ Billie ]
Scott's dead. I'm on my own.

986
01:07:48,097 --> 01:07:51,066
[ Little ]
This is Rattler. Do you copy?

987
01:07:51,167 --> 01:07:52,691
Night Rider Six.

988
01:07:52,768 --> 01:07:54,292
How many?

989
01:07:54,370 --> 01:07:57,396
They shot down Rives
and Tippet on take-off.

990
01:07:57,473 --> 01:07:59,600
Davis and Proctor are
with the Black Hawks.

991
01:08:05,581 --> 01:08:07,879
[ Little ]
Guthrie,you have...

992
01:08:08,117 --> 01:08:11,086
two bad boys looking
for something to do.

993
01:08:11,153 --> 01:08:12,848
Locate ground radar.

994
01:08:12,888 --> 01:08:15,482
When you find it,
we'll blow it up.

995
01:08:15,558 --> 01:08:18,356
I don't want them
knowing where we're at.

996
01:08:18,461 --> 01:08:20,224
[ Billie ]
Roger, Rattler.

997
01:08:20,830 --> 01:08:23,355
Rebel is hunting.

998
01:08:29,305 --> 01:08:31,330
Found it.
